Sentencas: A-site cation-ordered perovskite oxide LaBaCo2O5+delta (LBCO) was synthesized and evaluated as a cathode material of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization of cation-ordered perovskite oxide LaBaCo2O5+δ as cathode of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LBCO was structurally stable when calcined at 850 degrees C in air but transformed into cation-disordered structure at 1050 degrees C. LBCO showed chemical compatibility with Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (GDC) electrolyte at 850 degrees C and 1000 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Characterization of cation-ordered perovskite oxide LaBaCo2O5+δ as cathode of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Conductivity of LBCO firstly increased slightly with higher temperature to a maximum of 470 S cm(-1) at similar to 250 degrees C and then decreased gradually with further increase in temperature.
Titulo: Characterization of cation-ordered perovskite oxide LaBaCo2O5+δ as cathode of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectra of the LBCO/GDC/LBCO symmetric cell were measured, and electrode reaction mechanism for the LBCO cathode was analyzed.
Titulo: Characterization of cation-ordered perovskite oxide LaBaCo2O5+δ as cathode of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode polarization resistance of LBCO was mainly contributed by oxygen ionic transfer across the cathode/electrolyte interface and oxygen atom diffusion-electronic charge transfer process.
Titulo: Characterization of cation-ordered perovskite oxide LaBaCo2O5+δ as cathode of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Low area-specific resistances with values ranging from 0.15 Omega cm(2) at 650 degrees C to 0.0086 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C were obtained.
Titulo: Characterization of cation-ordered perovskite oxide LaBaCo2O5+δ as cathode of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results have demonstrated that the A-site cation-ordered perovskite oxide LBCO is a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of cation-ordered perovskite oxide LaBaCo2O5+δ as cathode of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
